1849
01:25:11,925 --> 01:25:15,136
<i>and it's always in many
cases, compromise.</i>

1850
01:25:15,220 --> 01:25:17,012
<i>And I think we were
fortunate in a lot of cases</i>

1851
01:25:17,096 --> 01:25:18,180
<i>not to have to compromise,</i>

1852
01:25:18,264 --> 01:25:22,351
<i>and, again, people like Randy
Fullmer and certainly Andy Gaskill,</i>

1853
01:25:22,435 --> 01:25:26,565
<i>helped us craft a look of the
