1854
01:25:26,649 --> 01:25:27,691
ALLERS: <i>They took us through places</i>

1855
01:25:27,775 --> 01:25:29,943
<i>where we had to cut back because of time.</i>

1856
01:25:30,027 --> 01:25:34,906
<i>And found other solutions
that would help us through it,</i>

1857
01:25:34,990 --> 01:25:39,286
<i>that would soften the absence, you know.</i>

1858
01:25:39,370 --> 01:25:42,205
<i>Like, for example, if we couldn't
do the certain effect in that one area,</i>

1859
01:25:42,289 --> 01:25:46,001
<i>they'd come up with another
solution that would be a simpler effect,</i>

1860
01:25:46,085 --> 01:25:49,421
<i>and yet it would keep
the production value up.</i>

1861
01:25:49,505 --> 01:25:51,548
<i>Their contribution is incredible.</i>

1862
01:25:51,632 --> 01:25:54,259
<i>So, you never had that sense
