1864
01:25:57,972 --> 01:26:01,141
<i>There was a lot of creative
monkeying going on back there,</i>

1865
01:26:01,225 --> 01:26:04,394
<i>in those colored model stations.</i>

1866
01:26:04,478 --> 01:26:06,188
HAHN: <i>That's a really good point.</i>

1867
01:26:06,272 --> 01:26:07,648
<i>Well, it's interesting
because a lot of people think</i>

1868
01:26:07,732 --> 01:26:10,401
<i>our characters and a lot of our
films are created by computer,</i>

1869
01:26:10,485 --> 01:26:12,153
<i>but nothing could be
further than the truth.</i>

1870
01:26:12,237 --> 01:26:15,907
<i>Because it's artists who have
always driven these movies</i>

1871
01:26:15,991 --> 01:26:17,742
<i>and certainly who have made</i> Lion King.

1872
01:26:17,826 --> 01:26:21,037
<i>So, in a way, animation's still
